This paper is primarily focused on object detection using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Deep Learning, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for low latency and real-time decision making, which could be related to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed framework also involves data reduction mechanisms, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a use-case for pedestrian detection from Unmanned-Areal-Vehicle (UAV), which could be related to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
